===Noun===
'''conkers''' (''British; plural and [[uncountable]]'')

#(''plural'') Plural of '''[[conker]]'''.
#(''uncountable'') A game for two players in which the each participant has a [[horse chestnut]] (known as a "conker") suspended from a length of string and  take it in turns to strike their opponent's [[conker]] with their own with the object of destroying one's opponent's conker before one's own is destroyed.

